  "body": "Multisig based stateRoot submission would possibly remove the 7 days challenge and on-chain fault prover.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/develop/packages/contracts-bedrock/src/L1/L2OutputOracle.sol#L176\r\n\r\nIf the multisig participants are trusted parties running some application to retrieve stateRoot with a dedicated resources I think there is no need to sacrifice users for the 7 days challenge period which would enhance user experience and would enable real-time L2 -> L1 data submission.\r\n\r\n( It would also enable running some gas costy operation with L2 from L1, for example Tornado Cash Nova does this with Gnosis Chain with the bridge. L1 -> L2 -> L1 )\r\n\r\nhttps://tornado-cash.medium.com/tornado-cash-introduces-arbitrary-amounts-shielded-transfers-8df92d93c37c\r\n",
